<br>
You wanna justify it on dots? Sure, but somehow if you were in the group for 2 hours, spend maybe 15 or 20 dots, and you take 1500pp gems from OS, it's a little off.<br>
<br>
You wanna justify it with the price of GAego scroll? Okay, I can dig that a lot more. But, are warriors going to be charging for the price of a fleshgrinder or cobolt? Hey, I'd be a more effective paladin if I had an MQ Skyshrine BP and loot rights to Tunare's 2hs. Heck, all melee could claim a CoF or RBG as expenses... all casters could claim FT3 boots. Hell, I am more effective with epic... should I charge for the cost of time and effort and money I spent on that?<br>
<br>
I say take your dot money. Hell, take twice or three times your dot money for times you don't get any gems. But split the rest, please. If I'm in the group and I didn't one of the top few rolls, and you, as a cleric, are pocketing enough gems for dots for a week... sorry, I have to agree, that's greedy.<br>
<br>
